--- D:\scripts\watch.ps1 ---
----[snip]----
(see file for full content — ~334 lines)

GitHub repo: https://github.com/Parth412100/MaelStream

Setup (one command):
  git clone https://github.com/Parth412100/MaelStream.git
  cd MaelStream
  .\setup.ps1

Flow:
  1. Pre-flight check — verifies Node.js, mpv, peerflix, webtorrent module
  2. Search TPB API (apibay.org?cat=0) for query — NOTE: cat=201 returns empty
  3. List results with seed counts, sorted by seeders (color-coded)
  4. User selects option:
     - Enter/#  → WebTorrent engine (default, auto-fallback ON)
     - 'p'      → Peerflix engine (no fallback)
     - 'a'      → aria2c engine (no fallback)
     - 'q'      → quit
  5. Stream selected movie via mpv with --cache=yes --cache-secs=120

Auto-fallback chain (when no engine explicitly chosen):
  WebTorrent (30s timeout) → Peerflix → aria2c → error

Engine details:
  - WebTorrent (default, engine 1):
      node stream-webtorrent.js <magnet> <port> <tempDir> <readyFile>
      Uses webtorrent@1.9.4 npm library (WebRTC + TCP + DHT peer discovery)
      Picks largest video file (.mkv/.mp4/.avi/.webm/.mov/.m4v/.flv/.wmv)
      Creates HTTP server with Range/seek support, writes readyFile signal
      Shows live progress: % | MB/s | ETA | peers
      Auto-exits after 180s timeout (30s in PowerShell waits for readyFile)
  - Peerflix (engine 2):
      peerflix $magnet --mpv -c 200 --remove
      Battle-tested, uses older torrent-stream backend
  - Aria2c (engine 3, fallback):
      aria2c downloads with 16 connections, max 200 peers, seed-time=0
      Waits up to 120s for first file chunk (>1MB)
      Then starts node stream-server.js <dir> <totalSize> <port> <readyFile>
      Serves partial file with Range support for mpv seeking
      NOTE: aria2c has no --sequential-download for BitTorrent; rarest-first only

Pre-flight dependency check (exits early with instructions if missing):
  - Node.js (via winget or manual)
  - mpv (via winget install "mpv-player.mpv-CI.MSVC")
  - peerflix (npm install -g peerflix)
  - webtorrent module (npm install in script dir)

All scripts avoid non-ASCII characters — em dashes/curly quotes would break
PowerShell parser on git clone with default encoding.

--- D:\scripts\stream-webtorrent.js ---
----[snip]----
(122 lines)
Node.js script that:
  - Takes: magnet, port, tempDir, readyFile
  - Uses webtorrent library (v1.9.4) to resolve magnet + download
  - Picks largest video file by extension order: mkv, mp4, avi, webm, mov, m4v, flv, wmv
  - Creates HTTP server on port with Range header support (206 for seeking)
  - Full non-range GET streams entire file (for init probes)
  - Writes readyFile when server.listen() fires
  - Progress interval every 2s: %, GB, MB/s, downloaded, ETA, peers
  - Auto-exits after 180s if no peers found
  - Handles client.on('error') for invalid magnets
  - SIGTERM/SIGINT: clean shutdown via client.destroy()
  - Disables uTP (utp: false) — TCP-only for reliability

--- D:\scripts\stream-server.js ---
----[snip]----
(93 lines)
Node.js script that:
  - Takes: downloadDir, totalFileSize, port[, readyFile]
