===========================================================================
 6. TROUBLESHOOTING
===========================================================================

--- "Connection refused" / mpv can't connect ---
  WebTorrent needs time to find peers. If no peers found:
  - Pick a torrent with 200+ seeders
  - Check Windows Firewall: allow node.exe, aria2c.exe on Private networks
  - Try 'p' for peerflix engine instead
  - Auto-fallback handles this: WebTorrent -> Peerflix -> aria2c

--- "TypeError: file.createServer is not a function" ---
  WebTorrent 2.x dropped File.createServer(). Run:
  npm install webtorrent@1.9.4
  (package.json pins to 1.9.4, but check if npm resolved a newer version)

--- "Missing token" / aria2c finds 0 peers ---
  ISP may block UDP tracker traffic. WebTorrent uses WebRTC (bypasses this).
  aria2c is only usable as fallback when other engines fail.
  ProtonVPN datacenter IPs also blocked by swarms — disconnect VPN for better P2P.

--- "All engines failed: webtorrent, peerflix, aria2c" ---
  ISP is blocking P2P entirely. Solutions:
  - Try torrent with 500+ seeders
  - Use VPN with P2P-optimized server (paid ProtonVPN, Mullvad)
  - Use debrid service (Real-Debrid ~$4/month) — caches via HTTPS
  - Try from different network (mobile hotspot)

--- "mpv.net installs as mpvnet.exe, not mpv.exe" ---
  Don't use mpv.net. Install official CI build:
  winget install "mpv-player.mpv-CI.MSVC"
  This gives you mpv.com + mpv.exe, not mpvnet.exe.

--- Setup.ps1 download times out ---
  shinchiro.mpv / GitHub downloads may time out from this network.
  Alternative: install mpv.net and copy mpvnet.exe -> mpv.exe, or retry.
  Official CI build (mpv-player.mpv-CI.MSVC) downloads ~73 MB.

--- Killed processes ---
  Run: Get-Process node,aria2c,mpv | Stop-Process -Force

--- "Cannot find webtorrent module" ---
  Run: cd D:\scripts && npm install
  (uses package.json, webtorrent pinned to 1.9.4)

--- Non-ASCII characters break PowerShell ---
  If git clone shows "Missing closing ')': if ($proc.HasExited -and !",
  the file has em dashes (U+2014) or curly quotes. All MaelStream scripts
  use only ASCII characters to avoid this.

--- "EPERM: operation not permitted" on npm install ---
  The ip-set package in webtorrent's dependency chain calls only-allow pnpm.
  Use webtorrent@1.9.4 (older version that avoids this).
  Fixed by pinning to 1.9.4 in package.json.

--- "peerflix is exiting" immediately ---
  Malformed magnet or tracker list too long. Auto-fallback handles this:
  WebTorrent or aria2c will be tried next.

--- "aria2c: unknown option -- sequential-download=true" ---
  --sequential-download doesn't exist for BitTorrent (HTTP/FTP only).
  Removed. aria2c downloads rarest-first; Node.js server handles seeking.

--- WinError 10061 (Connection refused) ---
  mpv started before the HTTP server was ready. Fixed by:
  - readyFile mechanism: Node.js writes a marker file when server.listen() fires
  - PowerShell polls for readyFile (30s timeout) before launching mpv
  - Both WebTorrent and aria2c engines use this now

